text: Cosipara molliculella is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Harrison Gray Dyar Jr. in 1929. It is found in Puebla, Mexico.Smithsonian Institution The wingspan is about 14 mm. Adults are similar to Cosipara cyclophora, but slightly smaller and greyer. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1929 Category:Scopariinae
title: Cosipara molliculella
